Thursday May 11.th 1893
Conn. building - fine old
Colonial style house painted yellow, with
white trimming - green blinds.
Paintings of Benedicts, Scovills, Coe Besse

down

Massachusetts building - copy

famous Massachusetts men on

Fine old furniture

New Hampshire building. Partly granite exterior. 
Kansas building. unfinished. corn, wheat & other farm products used in decoration. fancy designs of corn ears used. Sunflowers in
abundance - Upstairs paintings etc. in poor taste

Friday May 12th 
Entered at 62nd Street. Elevated road, inside grounds, getting view of buildings. I Fisheries building. Live turtles & fishes in aquarium part

II
Government building. Fine coral display. models of boats & fishes. House made of Californian tree. "The General Noble." Mules & army wagons- men in army uniforms of various periods. Puritan soldier with bible in hand Greely expedition. Flag that was displayed nearest North Pole. 1882-84. Paintings of Judges Supreme Court. Daniel Webster, John Jay.
Chase etc.

Worlds Fair Post Office is in this building (Government). Laplanders with dogs. old stage coach. Models of trains & steamboats. boys on bicycles. Stamp collection. Postal card collection. Columbian stamps of every kind. others in groups - years in which they were issued. Beautiful specimens agatized wood & minerals quartz Calcite (Pennsylvanian & Arizona) tourmaline (Maine) & Realaclute? fire (Arizona) quartz (white) Nevada

III
Friday afternoon. Woman's Building--Down stairs paintings etc. Upstairs - Lace from Venice Milan etc made 16th & 17th century. Etchings -1 lioness by Rosa Bonheur -
Nursing room -- Dolls dressed in various nurse's & hospital uniforms. modern appliances for Sick people - operations etc -

kitchen.
Pictures of women authors & poets etc of various periods ? these head "Poetry, Painting, Drama & music, Central? literature, Fiction, History & Science, pioneers in Education, & philanthropy. Royal ladies, 18th Century women. Civil wars," etc.
Japanese Room -- fine embroidered & painted screens etc - Bamboo & a ceiling -
In Cincinnati room. fine Rookwood pottery. Painted china -- Embroideries on linen,  Oil Painting on walls - carved furniture. White & gold room, just beyond

Children's building - entirely unfinished
In Horticultural Building -- Fine exhibit of apples & fruits from Oregon. Lots of canned fruit. Magnificent fruit (canned) from Washington State. Mammoth pears apples, plums, cherries, strawberries etc. also fresh fruit, potato 15in long, weighs 5 lbs. Missouri fruits, Ontario fruits, Idaho fruits -- potatoes a specialty, New Mexico fruits grapes fine

pillar of solid (real) oranges from "Citrus Belt of Southern California" (Los Angeles county). Illinois exhibit of fruit (mostly apples). Minnesota exhibit. Wisconsin Ex.
California exhibit oranges & citrus of great variety. Iowa fruits. Germany (artificial fruits)

Conservatory department with palms etc growing in rotunda. In this part is a Reproduction of Mammoth Crystal cave of Black Hills, South Dakota (largest cave in the world. 1400 rooms have been now discovered, over 52 miles of underground rooms. 18 miles from Deadwood, South Dakota
Fine palms & ferns grand orchids etc. in Pitcher & Wanda's? display. in same room is a fine palm (Massachusetts) "Dickinsonia regalis" from H.H. Hunnewell, Wellesley Mass (like unclear ferns) Fine ex of calciolaria (reticule flower)

Galveston Texas display. Opposite unclear given up to British exhibit of palms from unclear & Australia. British unclear of gilt - very large
Except one part for Japan.
Transportation building. Carriages of finest styles made by Studebaker of South Bend, Krieball of Chicago, Manville ? New Haven etc - Tally ho's etc - Deere's (Moline) plows
Steam rollers -- "Canadian Pacific" train complete - Engine, 1st & 2nd class cars; dining car & baggage car.
Five? models of ocean steamships - Laker? "Arizona" etc. Steam yachts etc.

Convent of La Rabida. Paintings etc of Columbus see guide book.
Agricultural Building. Washington State exhibit. New Jersey, Missouri, etc. of wheats, corn etc. in fancy decoration of booths
French Exhibit. unclear unclear tower built of packages (green) production of one day. canned goods
Denmark exhibit in unclear

Denmark exhibit  m from of farm house. pictures of various peasant costumes
Ontario exhibit. very fine exhibit. of wheat corn rye unclear etc in glass - also in sheaves for decoration
Canadian cheese - weight 22000 pounds - made in one day at Perth Ontario
Ohio booth with many columns of glass filled with seeds bean etc. Illinois - fine booth mosaic of corn in various colors. unclear - Iowa (soil in various glass pillars- 
Crosse & Blackwell

Maillards chocolate. Stollberg's chocolate (Cologne). French section. School of agriculture. showing methods of teaching. South American (Paraguay) exhibit - leaves
roots & herbs -- Fibrous plants. Bock beer. Spanish exhibit unclear. Austria

Ceylon. New South Wales, Australia. Wool (natural state in quantities unclear exhibit-
Quebec - grains. Cape of Good Hope. Ostrich feathers, eggs and birds
Lunch at Casino

Midway Plaisance. International dress & costumes (of Women) Exhibit Building. Irish village & industries - Bog wood carving. girl spinning. Beleek ware
Blarney Castle (facsimile) 79 steps to top of it. Irish flag on top, flying
New England Kitchen etc. in log cabin, big fire place with

big fire place with logs burning & kettle - old presser with pewter & other plates spinning wheels, warming pan, old cradle made of barrel, painted & put on rockers, old chairs etc
Bedroom, with four posted bed.
Vienna Cafe-- Natatorium-- Beer tunnel?
Sedan chairs - for 15 minutes, made by Studebaker Bros South Bend Indiana

Constantinople - Fine brass embossed & unclear jars & utensils trays etc. Turkish fire engines - (portable). Exterior carved inlaid brown wood made in Turkey & unclear
E. India building one of the most beauty unclear unfinished. Dilly? man talked to us there - showed us around building, gallery upstairs -- fine copper work embossed & openwork. Kashmir rugs. models of "unclear" Indian factory - Silver & gold ware -- vases carved ivory unclearunclear & brass gods - silks- Beautiful finely carved ebony

Pullman cars - &Pullman Electric cars. cars made in 1836. English train - "Northwestern & London." Elevator swimming jackets Turkish sedan chairs & donkey baskets & saddles
for riding - 
Horticultural building for luncheon - (2nd visit). Model of U.S. Capitol of Washington D.C. made of everlasting flowers.  The grounds laid out with real earth & plants.
Upsatirs Model of Horticultural building of unclear

Horticultural building of unclear unclear Linderhof (Bavaria) Castle & grounds photographed & place planted in water colors of the grounds.
Illinois building -- very large - Fine exhibit of grains & canned fruits etc. Picture & frame made entirely of grains & grasses, on wall -- very well done representing farm house & fields.

V Tuesday May 16
Indiana building. very pretty & in good taste stained glass windows. rooms finished in oak down stairs, tiled floors, handsome fireplaces. exterior staff and stucco grey.
Wisconsin building. more finished than most of them. oak unclear - tiled floor. exterior brown stone & wood & brick (lower story). 4 stories high. fireplace tiled green like ours at home. Succesive framed "history of Wisconsin" stained glass window unclear scenery from Wisconsin.
Ohio building--white

Ohio building - white exterior - very good taste within - Cincinnati room especially. Cleveland room. things made for entertaining in Cleveland, dark blue carpet and furnishings mostly paintings by entrance to building of Hayes & Sherman.
Michigan building. very large frame house grey - 3 floors - clock in tower. unclear fireplace 1st floor biggest we've seen yet. Upstairs stuffed animals. elks, deer, bears, foxes, birds, etc. fine exhibit.

Washington State building. big logs at base, gray stone & stucco (exterior). Inside grains, canned fruit. big model of farm in center of principal hall. farm house, fields of grain, cows, horses, barns etc. fine. coal from different regions of state - stone, gold & silver ore. section of unclear trees. 77 kinds of timber shown. One cedar measuring 18 1/2 feet in diameter unclear the ground -- (taken from Gray's Harbor). "Western Hemlock" lovely fir "Vine Maple" "Alaska cedar" "Pacific Coast wax maple" "Red or pencil cedar" "Upland willow" "Maple burl" etc.

Ores--"gold lead, zinc silver iron copper, antimony and other metals found in Washington State. Enormous skeleton of antediluvian lesotho models of fishes found in Washington State. 
Minnesota, exterior very white carved (unknown).
Inside stuffed deers, bears etc. (birds?)
Model of St. Lukes' Hospital samples of "Kasota pink limestone and others and samples of Minnesota woods. 
Gasification of stairway walls of three (3) deers' heads with horns beaming electric lights.
Upstairs St. Paul at right and Minneapolis at left of stairway. Indian curios of pipestone.

made by Indiana of Minnesota--pipestone is only found in Minnesota. unknown and soft, fireplace partly made of it. Hearthstone of jasper stone (old red)
Beautiful shells (downstairs) from the Minnesota River. Fine display near these of Minnesota Indians' work moccasins drums painted, etc.
Wisconsin building--walls decorated with minerals (jasper quartz more ) ceiling very fine--dull tans blues and browns. yellow of tenor.

"Minnesota" arch of stone of various kinds with names of cities one on each.  Duluth the keystone of the arch.  opposite this is the Asbestos exhibit.  shows it being made  Asbestos is found near Quebec in large quantities - thousands of tons are quarried in rock form - is crushed with sort of stone crusher so as not to destroy fibre, then put into a "picker" separated & then spun & woven into cloth -

Esquimaus
This is a project gotten up by Spokane native $10,000 spent to get them [[?] here
Esquimaux village about 30
Mission near & woman more civilized than some
Esquimau prince 16 yrs. old very small & boy like in looks.  Thickset.  
Very dirty people - Straight black hair - dark as negroes - look some like Chinese. flatfaced.  Man in sealskin hood & shirt out rowing in canoe in true Esquimau style
Dogs 25 of them about.  Were using their long leather whips
